* Version number criteria

  We use the version numbering criteria with a major and a minor
  number revision, following:

  - "The major version of your library starts at zero and is
    incremented if the library breaks backwards compatibility."
  - "The minor version of your library also starts at zero. Every time
    you add to the libraries interface but maintain backwards
    compatibility, this is incremented. If you bump the major version,
    it is reset to zero."
  - The minor number is a composition of two numbers, the first one
    indicates the stability of the code (even = stable, odd =
    unstable).

* Version number change

  To change the version number you have to edit entry

  <property name="version.num" value="0.4.3" />
 
  in file build.xml of the netbeans project.
